radiographic_examinations.findings: Mild atelectasis at the lung bases, no pleural effusions, normal heart size with trace pericardial effusion, small hiatal hernia, scattered tiny hypodensities in the liver, moderate intrahepatic biliary dilation, partially distended gallbladder with an 11-mm calcified gallstone, mild circumferential gallbladder wall edema, normal pancreas, non-dilated pancreatic duct, normal spleen, normal kidneys, normal stomach and duodenum, non-dilated appendix, unremarkable colon and rectum, normal bladder, normal uterus and ovaries, mild multilevel degenerative changes in the thoracolumbar spine.
